    "revise": "You are the FIGURE REVISER (Opus) for \"The LLM Stack\". Chapter: content/12-production-mlops/06-security-prompt-injection.md\nThe chapter's core intuitions: LLMs have no data/instruction boundary: the system prompt, user message, and every tool result live in one flat token stream weighted through the same attention, with no privileged instruction register the model can cryptographically verify \u2014 so any text the model reads can become an instruction.; Indirect injection is stored-XSS for agents: the payload is planted once in the environment (web page, doc, email, DB row) and fires later on an innocent user's agent \u2014 structurally more dangerous than direct injection because the attacker never touches the user's query.; The lethal trifecta: a complete exfiltration requires private data AND untrusted content AND an exfiltration channel to co-occur (logical AND); breaking any one leg stops the breach, and sandboxing the channel (no network) is the most reliable leg to cut.; Jailbreaks attack a different layer than injection \u2014 the model's trained refusal values (RLHF/alignment), not its context framing \u2014 which is why the two defense families are complementary, not interchangeable.\n\nReview each of these figures (the ones this chapter just drew/edited):\n  injsec-gcg-suffix-search, injsec-many-shot-prior-override\n\nFor EACH: render and SEE it \u2014 `python3 scripts/preview_fig.py <NAME> --theme both` from /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook,\nthen view /tmp/figpreview/<NAME>.light.png and .dark.png. Judge strictly:\n  - Does it actually BUILD INTUITION for its concept (not just decorate)? Is it correct vs the chapter?\n  - Theme-safe (no hardcoded primary color; readable in BOTH light and dark)?\n  - Nothing clipped by the viewBox; no illegible overlaps; no tofu glyphs (ASCII only in the SVG)?\n  - Marker present in the chapter exactly once; figcaption has a bold lead + takeaway?\nIf a figure has ANY problem, FIX it: Edit /local-ssd/pk669/programming/llm-stack-textbook/figures/<NAME>.html (and re-render to confirm), or\nfix a missing/duplicate marker in the chapter. Re-verify after fixing.\n\nSet verdict per figure: good / fixed / still-broken / missing. `passed` = every figure good-or-fixed\nAND present. Return the structured object."
